const faqs = [
  { question: 'What types of pigment spots can be treated?', answer: 'We can treat sun spots, age spots, pregnancy melasma, freckles, and other discolorations caused by melanin overproduction with the Nd:YAG laser. During the consultation, we determine the type of spot and the appropriate treatment method.' },
  { question: 'Is pigment spot removal painful?', answer: 'The treatment may cause a mild stinging or warm sensation. Most of our clients tolerate it well and do not require anesthesia.' },
  { question: 'How many treatments are needed?', answer: 'Generally, 1 treatment is sufficient to achieve the desired result. If the nature of the pigmentation requires a repeat treatment, the fee is 50% of the current treatment price.' },
  { question: 'When will I see results?', answer: 'A temporary scab may form on the treated area, which typically falls off naturally within 7-10 days, depending on the individual. The result becomes visible after this.' },
  { question: 'Is there any downtime?', answer: 'The treated area may have a scab for 7-10 days. Makeup is not allowed while there is a scab on the skin. During the healing period, the treated area should be cared for with a special cream and SPF 50 sunscreen.' },
  { question: 'What season is best to start treatment?', answer: 'Fall and winter are ideal when there is less sun exposure. It can also be done in summer with increased sun protection, but sunbathing should be avoided before and after treatment.' },
